Hey! You gotta
protect yourself!

46
00:02:02,989 --> 00:02:04,989
Bakuzan: Carnage punch!

47
00:02:05,059 --> 00:02:07,592
( Laughs )

48
00:02:07,661 --> 00:02:11,930
I'll give you one last chance
to apologize for our match.

49
00:02:11,998 --> 00:02:13,866
( Laughs )

50
00:02:13,934 --> 00:02:16,401
( Sighs ) Party pooper.

51
00:02:16,403 --> 00:02:18,002
Must have gone into shock
or something.

52
00:02:18,004 --> 00:02:19,471
Time to end this.

53
00:02:19,540 --> 00:02:22,407
I'll get rid of all of you
in one fell swoop!

54
00:02:22,409 --> 00:02:23,942
Hell-bringin' hand chop!

55
00:02:24,010 --> 00:02:25,444
Saitama: Nope,
I just don't remember him.

56
00:02:27,481 --> 00:02:29,682
( Suiryu gasps )

57
00:02:31,285 --> 00:02:33,752
Saitama: No idea who that was.

58
00:02:33,820 --> 00:02:34,753
Meh.

59
00:02:34,821 --> 00:02:36,889
¶

60
00:02:36,957 --> 00:02:39,758
- ( suiryu gasps )
- Saitama: Man, that must have

61
00:02:39,826 --> 00:02:42,827
really sucked for you
after winning the tournament.

62
00:02:42,829 --> 00:02:45,029
Well, maybe, next time,

63
00:02:45,099 --> 00:02:46,899
there'll be
less monsters around.

64
00:02:46,967 --> 00:02:48,701
Suiryu: Uh, yeah,

65
00:02:48,769 --> 00:02:51,770
and thanks for saving me
and everything.

66
00:02:51,838 --> 00:02:54,706
Tell me, who are you,
I mean, really?

67
00:02:54,775 --> 00:02:58,042
Saitama: I'm saitama.
I'm a hero.

68
00:02:58,112 --> 00:03:00,645
Suiryu: Saitama? So...

69
00:03:00,714 --> 00:03:03,047
That means charanko
was just an alias, wasn't it?

70
00:03:03,049 --> 00:03:04,583
Saitama: Uh, crap.

71
00:03:04,651 --> 00:03:07,586
Suiryu: I don't get it.
What were you doing here?

72
00:03:07,654 --> 00:03:10,455
Some undercover mission
for the hero association?

73
00:03:10,524 --> 00:03:12,925
Saitama: No. I wanted
to experience martial arts

74
00:03:12,993 --> 00:03:14,793
and bag that prize money.

75
00:03:14,861 --> 00:03:18,330
There's this guy
calling himself a hero hunter.

76
00:03:18,399 --> 00:03:21,333
They say
he's a martial arts master,

77
00:03:21,401 --> 00:03:23,535
so it kinda piqued my interest,
you know?

78
00:03:23,604 --> 00:03:26,605
Suiryu: I see. You were looking
for ways to counter him.

79
00:03:26,673 --> 00:03:29,341
Saitama: Well, I wouldn't
exactly say that was the reason.

80
00:03:29,409 --> 00:03:32,477
I just happened upon
an entry ticket.

81
00:03:32,479 --> 00:03:34,813
And, to be completely honest...

82
00:03:36,483 --> 00:03:38,150
- ( Music stops )
- I was bored.

83
00:03:38,218 --> 00:03:39,884
Suiryu:
You've gotta be kidding me.

84
00:03:39,886 --> 00:03:43,422
Still,
it's thanks to you I'm alive.

85
00:03:43,490 --> 00:03:45,690
Saitama: Sorry I
didn't get here sooner.

86
00:03:45,759 --> 00:03:48,026
- Suiryu: Wait! Saitama...
- Saitama: Huh?

87
00:03:48,094 --> 00:03:50,028
Suiryu: Please,
you shouldn't go out there.

88
00:03:50,097 --> 00:03:51,830
There's this group raising hell.

89
00:03:51,898 --> 00:03:53,498
They call themselves
the monster association,

90
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:54,566
and they're bad news.

91
00:03:54,635 --> 00:03:56,368
- Saitama: For real?
- Suiryu: Yeah.

92
00:03:56,437 --> 00:03:58,436
And what's worse
is that they have the ability

93
00:03:58,505 --> 00:04:00,038
to transform humans
into monsters, too.

94
00:04:00,107 --> 00:04:02,641
That guy you just beat
was one of them.

95
00:04:02,709 --> 00:04:04,843
Remember bakuzan,
your second match?

96
00:04:04,911 --> 00:04:06,979
Saitama: Oh,
so that's who he was.

97
00:04:07,047 --> 00:04:08,513
I mean, it's hard for me

98
00:04:08,515 --> 00:04:10,715
to remember
every opponent I punch.

99
00:04:10,717 --> 00:04:13,718
Suiryu: The point is, it's
dangerous out there right now.

100
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:15,587
I think it's best if we lay low.

101
00:04:15,656 --> 00:04:17,656
Goketsu's out there.
We should avoid him.

102
00:04:17,724 --> 00:04:19,591
Saitama: Goketsu?

103
00:04:19,660 --> 00:04:22,527
Suiryu: Another monster
that used to be human.

104
00:04:22,529 --> 00:04:25,063
I threw everything I had at him,

105
00:04:25,131 --> 00:04:26,665
but it didn't do a damn thing.

106
00:04:26,733 --> 00:04:29,668
That strength, it was horrific.

107
00:04:29,736 --> 00:04:31,804
( Rotors whirring )

108
00:04:31,872 --> 00:04:33,738
Genos: When my repairs are done,

109
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:35,073
I must return at once.

110
00:04:35,142 --> 00:04:36,941
Even if he caught me off-guard,

111
00:04:36,943 --> 00:04:39,478
a monster that can beat me
with one punch

112
00:04:39,546 --> 00:04:41,613
must not be allowed to survive.

113
00:04:41,682 --> 00:04:44,082
I need to assemble
the class-s heroes

114
00:04:44,151 --> 00:04:47,752
with master saitama,
then strike together.

115
00:04:47,822 --> 00:04:50,154
Saitama: So this guy's
pretty strong, huh?

116
00:04:50,156 --> 00:04:52,557
Suiryu: Even with
the most meticulous preparation,

117
00:04:52,559 --> 00:04:54,159
I'm not sure
if anyone can beat him.

118
00:04:54,228 --> 00:04:55,160
Saitama: I see.

119
00:04:55,229 --> 00:04:58,163
So where did this monster go?

120
00:04:58,165 --> 00:05:00,432
Suiryu: Um, through that wall.

121
00:05:00,501 --> 00:05:01,700
Saitama: Ah.

122
00:05:01,768 --> 00:05:03,635
So all that noise earlier
was him, huh?

123
00:05:03,704 --> 00:05:05,504
I'll check it out.

124
00:05:05,572 --> 00:05:07,706
Suiryu: No!
Weren't you listening to me?

125
00:05:07,774 --> 00:05:10,042
I told you! He's unstoppable!

126
00:05:10,110 --> 00:05:11,844
Saitama: I heard you. No prob.

127
00:05:11,912 --> 00:05:13,778
Suiryu: You still
don't get it, do you?!

128
00:05:13,848 --> 00:05:17,516
Goketsu was once a famous
and exceptional martial artist.

129
00:05:17,584 --> 00:05:19,784
He's dangerous.
You'll be killed for sure!

130
00:05:19,854 --> 00:05:22,521
Saitama: Whoa.
A martial arts master, huh?

131
00:05:22,589 --> 00:05:24,989
Perfect. It might help
my indigestion.

132
00:05:24,991 --> 00:05:26,725
- ( Suiryu groans )
- Saitama: Uh...

133
00:05:26,793 --> 00:05:29,594
Hey, you're injured.
Take it easy.

134
00:05:29,663 --> 00:05:31,063
Suiryu: I'm not letting go.

135
00:05:31,131 --> 00:05:34,366
I won't let you throw away
your life when I owe you mine!

136
00:05:35,602 --> 00:05:38,937
( Groaning )

137
00:05:39,005 --> 00:05:40,773
¶

138
00:05:45,679 --> 00:05:47,513
( crying )

139
00:05:52,687 --> 00:05:55,620
( Grunts )
I just couldn't stop him.

140
00:05:55,622 --> 00:05:57,056
( Sighs )

141
00:05:58,225 --> 00:06:00,024
( Boom )

142
00:06:00,094 --> 00:06:02,026
- I think I get it now.
- ( Booming continues )

143
00:06:02,096 --> 00:06:06,030
I finally understand
what it means to be a true hero!

144
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:08,166
And now he's going
to throw his life away.

145
00:06:08,235 --> 00:06:09,834
What a waste.

146
00:06:09,836 --> 00:06:12,705
Saitama was destined
to save so many more people.

147
00:06:12,773 --> 00:06:14,239
( Crying )

148
00:06:14,241 --> 00:06:15,607
( Gasps )

149
00:06:24,651 --> 00:06:25,984
Saitama: Oh, by the way,

150
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:28,120
there's something
I forgot to mention earlier.

151
00:06:28,188 --> 00:06:31,123
That thing about me lying
to get into the tournament,

152
00:06:31,191 --> 00:06:32,524
( whispering )
Could we keep it a secret?

153
00:06:32,593 --> 00:06:34,859
Suiryu: Uh...

154
00:06:34,861 --> 00:06:38,130
So was goketsu
tough to take down?

155
00:06:38,198 --> 00:06:40,865
Saitama: Well, when they
only take one punch,

156
00:06:40,935 --> 00:06:42,667
it's kinda hard to compare.

157
00:06:42,736 --> 00:06:44,937
Suiryu: There's something else
I want to ask you.

158
00:06:45,005 --> 00:06:46,538
Saitama: What's up?

159
00:06:46,607 --> 00:06:48,807
Suiryu: I don't know
if I could overcome my fear,

160
00:06:48,875 --> 00:06:51,009
but I'd like to try,
and, if I did,

161
00:06:51,078 --> 00:06:54,146
do you think
I can become a hero?

162
00:06:54,214 --> 00:06:56,748
- Saitama: I don't know.
- Suiryu: Huh?

163
00:06:56,817 --> 00:06:59,551
Saitama: But, you know,
if I became one,

164
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:00,953
then I think maybe anybody can.

165
00:07:01,021 --> 00:07:04,222
It's natural
to be afraid at the start.

166
00:07:04,291 --> 00:07:08,226
I mean, before I got too strong,
I was scared, too.

167
00:07:08,295 --> 00:07:10,028
Suiryu: A hero who's too strong?

168
00:07:10,097 --> 00:07:12,631
Not bad. Not bad.

169
00:07:12,699 --> 00:07:16,101
Oh! Can I ask you
another question, saitama?

170
00:07:16,170 --> 00:07:17,770
- Saitama: Sure.
- ( Suiryu chuckles )

171
00:07:17,838 --> 00:07:20,104
Could I be your disciple?

172
00:07:20,106 --> 00:07:21,105
( Saitama chuckles )

173
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:23,575
Absolutely not.

174
00:07:23,644 --> 00:07:25,243
¶

175
00:07:25,312 --> 00:07:26,779
puri-puri prisoner: Damn it.

176
00:07:26,847 --> 00:07:29,181
His whole body's
covered in spikes.

177
00:07:29,249 --> 00:07:31,583
How do I fight him?

178
00:07:31,652 --> 00:07:33,251
Man: Prisoner!
Don't use your hands on him!

179
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:35,320
Man 2: Use your ball and chain
to pound him senseless!

180
00:07:35,389 --> 00:07:37,121
Man 1: Yeah!
Make him hug your ball!

181
00:07:37,123 --> 00:07:38,991
Puri-puri prisoner:
Hmm? I thank you

182
00:07:39,059 --> 00:07:40,993
for your words
of encouragement, gentlemen.

183
00:07:41,061 --> 00:07:43,127
You'll get kisses
of gratitude later,

184
00:07:43,129 --> 00:07:44,997
but, for now,
I must insist that you flee!

185
00:07:45,065 --> 00:07:47,932
Man 3: No use.
He can't hear a word.

186
00:07:48,002 --> 00:07:50,803
Man 1: So, does he have
to fight completely naked, or...

187
00:07:50,871 --> 00:07:53,271
Puri-puri prisoner:
You fresh-faced boys so bravely

188
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:57,209
cheering me on like this,
your love will not be forgotten!

189
00:07:57,277 --> 00:07:59,144
Love! ( Gasps )

190
00:07:59,213 --> 00:08:02,681
That's it. That's the answer.

191
00:08:02,749 --> 00:08:05,950
I can accept the pain
with love so deep

192
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:08,754
there will be
nothing left to fear!

193
00:08:10,290 --> 00:08:11,223
( Monster groans )

194
00:08:11,291 --> 00:08:13,291
Puri-puri prisoner: Angel hug!

195
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:14,860
- ( Cracking )
- ( Monster screaming )

196
00:08:18,632 --> 00:08:19,832
Puri-puri prisoner: Love!

197
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:21,766
Man 4: He keeps staring at us...

198
00:08:21,768 --> 00:08:23,035
Bloody and naked.

199
00:08:23,103 --> 00:08:24,302
( Cell phone buzzing )

200
00:08:24,371 --> 00:08:26,104
Puri-puri prisoner: Yes, hello.

201
00:08:26,173 --> 00:08:27,239
You've got puri-puri.

202
00:08:27,307 --> 00:08:29,174
What?

203
00:08:29,243 --> 00:08:33,111
It broke into my comfy,
cozy home and stole my honeys?

204
00:08:33,180 --> 00:08:35,614
- ( Crack )
- And where is this monster now?

205
00:08:37,117 --> 00:08:39,784
- Saitama: They're gone?
- Hero: Yeah.

206
00:08:39,854 --> 00:08:43,121
They all left together
about 30 minutes ago.

207
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:44,789
Saitama: So they
arrived as a group,

208
00:08:44,859 --> 00:08:47,392
went crazy,
and then left all at once?

209
00:08:47,461 --> 00:08:50,128
What were they up to?

210
00:08:50,197 --> 00:08:54,666
Damn it. How did I miss
such a huge disaster?

211
00:08:54,735 --> 00:08:56,669
The other heroes
were out here fighting.

212
00:08:56,737 --> 00:08:59,404
Man, what was I thinking?

213
00:08:59,473 --> 00:09:02,407
Crushing monsters
is my job, right?

214
00:09:02,409 --> 00:09:04,209
( Grunts ) Wait a second.

215
00:09:04,278 --> 00:09:08,280
I don't fight monsters
just because I wanted a job.

216
00:09:08,348 --> 00:09:10,148
That's not it at all.

217
00:09:10,217 --> 00:09:13,218
I might have forgotten
something important,

218
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:15,820
like the reason I became a hero
in the first place

219
00:09:15,890 --> 00:09:19,758
I mean, I started out
just having fun,

220
00:09:19,826 --> 00:09:22,227
but, since joining
the hero association,

221
00:09:22,296 --> 00:09:25,029
I've been bored out of my mind.

222
00:09:25,031 --> 00:09:28,233
That hero-hunter guy
got me curious again.

223
00:09:28,235 --> 00:09:30,769
That's the reason I entered
the martial arts tournament.

224
00:09:32,038 --> 00:09:35,774
But, against suiryu
and the others,

225
00:09:35,842 --> 00:09:39,177
even against a monster
who was a master martial artist,

226
00:09:39,246 --> 00:09:42,114
I didn't really feel anything.

227
00:09:42,182 --> 00:09:43,982
I didn't get
anything out of it.

228
00:09:44,050 --> 00:09:46,719
- ( Brakes squeal )
- King: Saitama. Hey.

229
00:09:46,787 --> 00:09:47,720
Saitama: Hmm?

230
00:09:48,923 --> 00:09:50,389
Hey, king.

231
00:09:50,457 --> 00:09:51,924
( Wind blowing )

232
00:09:51,992 --> 00:09:54,326
Are you sure
it's safe to be out here?

233
00:09:54,394 --> 00:09:57,729
King: Well, I heard
all those alarms going off,

234
00:09:57,798 --> 00:09:59,464
but it seems to be
pretty quiet now.

235
00:09:59,466 --> 00:10:02,267
What's wrong?
You look kinda bummed.

236
00:10:02,336 --> 00:10:05,870
Saitama: I, uh--
I got a lot on my mind.

237
00:10:05,872 --> 00:10:08,073
King: I get it,
but, hey, you're still young.

238
00:10:08,142 --> 00:10:10,875
- Don't go giving up yet.
- Saitama: Thanks, man.

239
00:10:10,877 --> 00:10:12,877
King: I mean,
there's still a decent chance

240
00:10:12,947 --> 00:10:15,079
it might grow back. Plus, uh,
there are treatments--

241
00:10:15,081 --> 00:10:16,281
saitama: Whoa, whoa! Wait a sec!

242
00:10:16,350 --> 00:10:17,482
That's not
what I'm talking about!

243
00:10:17,551 --> 00:10:20,352
It's more
of a big-picture thing.

244
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:21,820
King: Ah, gotcha.

245
00:10:21,888 --> 00:10:23,155
But being down isn't like you.

246
00:10:23,223 --> 00:10:24,889
You're always so strong.

247
00:10:24,959 --> 00:10:26,891
Saitama: Well, I'm not
gonna be getting any stronger.

248
00:10:26,961 --> 00:10:29,094
- I know that much.
- King: What?

249
00:10:29,163 --> 00:10:32,030
Saitama: I'm saying
I've become too strong.

250
00:10:32,098 --> 00:10:34,833
No matter who I fight,
I don't feel anything.

