themselves as our rivals,

498
00:20:44,044 --> 00:20:46,845
implementing a method for
turning humans into monsters.

499
00:20:46,914 --> 00:20:49,848
Their leader is known
as the "monster king," orochi.

500
00:20:49,850 --> 00:20:52,384
We've also received
the approximate location

501
00:20:52,452 --> 00:20:55,921
of their lair. It's city z's
abandoned ghost town.

502
00:20:55,989 --> 00:20:58,056
Man 2: The area
that was taken by the monsters.

503
00:20:58,125 --> 00:21:00,726
Man 3: This monster association
went through a lot of trouble

504
00:21:00,794 --> 00:21:02,460
to kidnap an executive's son.

505
00:21:02,530 --> 00:21:04,796
Perhaps it means
they want to negotiate.

506
00:21:04,865 --> 00:21:06,732
Man 4: Yes.
It's their way of saying,

507
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:09,401
"don't try anything stupid."
Perhaps they're hoping

508
00:21:09,469 --> 00:21:11,403
they can talk their way
out of extermination.

509
00:21:11,471 --> 00:21:13,339
Anything's possible.

510
00:21:13,407 --> 00:21:15,673
Man 3: There's a thought.
If the ghost town monsters

511
00:21:15,743 --> 00:21:18,476
formed some sort of coalition,
that would add up.

512
00:21:18,478 --> 00:21:20,812
Sitch: The kidnapping,
the riots, the chaos,

513
00:21:20,881 --> 00:21:22,614
everything that happened
could have been

514
00:21:22,682 --> 00:21:24,416
their way of staging a protest.

515
00:21:24,484 --> 00:21:26,352
These aren't random acts.

516
00:21:26,420 --> 00:21:27,619
These monsters possess

517
00:21:27,687 --> 00:21:28,754
the intellect and will

518
00:21:28,822 --> 00:21:30,622
to act as a group.

519
00:21:30,690 --> 00:21:32,891
I feel the likelihood
that they will reach out to us

520
00:21:32,893 --> 00:21:34,025
is extremely high.

521
00:21:34,094 --> 00:21:36,895
Man 2: That's not
a bad strategy.

522
00:21:36,897 --> 00:21:38,030
We could end this,

523
00:21:38,098 --> 00:21:40,032
approach them as a ruse,
then wipe them out.

524
00:21:40,100 --> 00:21:42,768
Woman: Let's hear
what they have to say first.

525
00:21:42,836 --> 00:21:46,037
Our primary objective remains
the safe return of the hostage.

526
00:21:46,106 --> 00:21:48,506
Man 5: Correct.
Esteemed advisor narinki

527
00:21:48,576 --> 00:21:50,576
is by far one of our top donors.

528
00:21:50,644 --> 00:21:54,112
If anything happened to his son,
he would surely cut us off.

529
00:21:54,181 --> 00:21:56,382
The boy must be rescued. Hmm?

530
00:21:56,450 --> 00:21:59,717
Man 6: We've received a message
from the monster association!

531
00:21:59,719 --> 00:22:02,388
We've received a message
from the monster association!

532
00:22:02,456 --> 00:22:03,721
Sitch: What is it?

533
00:22:03,723 --> 00:22:04,722
Man 6: We've received
a message...

534
00:22:04,792 --> 00:22:06,392
Man 4: Tell us!

535
00:22:06,460 --> 00:22:08,126
Man 5: I think
something's wrong with him.

536
00:22:08,128 --> 00:22:09,527
Man 6: We've received a message

537
00:22:09,529 --> 00:22:11,597
from the monster association.

538
00:22:11,665 --> 00:22:14,933
We've received a message--
( Screams )

539
00:22:14,935 --> 00:22:16,868
Monster: I said
we've received a message

540
00:22:16,937 --> 00:22:19,004
from the monster association.

541
00:22:21,075 --> 00:22:23,909
( Sizzling )

542
00:22:23,911 --> 00:22:25,377
¶

543
00:22:29,617 --> 00:22:33,751
Sonic: I'm sure it was the right
call to cook this thing.

544
00:22:33,753 --> 00:22:35,020
Common sense says it's not safe

545
00:22:35,089 --> 00:22:37,756
to eat meat like this
while it's still raw.

546
00:22:37,825 --> 00:22:40,959
I'll try not to think about it.

547
00:22:41,028 --> 00:22:43,028
( Laughs )

548
00:22:43,097 --> 00:22:45,163
I'm coming for you, saitama.

549
00:22:45,232 --> 00:22:47,032
Watch your back.

